    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nFor lsp_lines.nvim, some users want error diagnostics to be wrapped ([related issue](https://todo.sr.ht/~whynothugo/lsp_lines.nvim/46))\r\n\r\nThe current virtual text API does not allow for me to indicate \"this text may be wrapped\". Given that the virtual text is per-buffer, manually wrapping the text would produce awkward results. In particular, wrapping could be wrong for one split if the same buffer is shown on two vertical splits of different width.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI would like an API to either:\r\n\r\n- Indicate that virtual text can be wrapped, or\r\n- Indicate that virtual text may wrap if wrapping is enabled for a given buffer.\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2024-01-05T06:14:58Z",
